  Name: The human lungs
  Description: The human lungs are vital, spongy organs that power the respiratory
    system. They draw essential oxygen into the bloodstream and expel carbon dioxide
    as waste. Inside, millions of tiny air sacs called alveoli maximize this crucial
    gas exchange.
